They had stay’d long enough to see, In Thebes, the billow of calamity Over their own dear children roll’‚d Curse upon curse, pang upon pang, For years, they sitting helpless in their home, A grey old man and woman; yet of old The gods had to their marriage corne And at the banquet all the Muses sang’.
